Hi, 
I am trying to compile Altera's RAM, it has a construct as shown below. Now all these signals are connected to their Altsync Module, but when I try to check the signals in GTKWave it does not show me any of the signals, I suspect verilator is messing with the tristate signals cause if I comment tri1 rden I am able to get the signal. Can you tell me if this is a known issue and if yes is there a workaround?

	input	  clock;
	input	[31:0]  data;
	input	[11:0]  rdaddress;
	input	  rden;
	input	[11:0]  wraddress;
	input	  wren;
	output	[31:0]  q;
	tri1	  clock;
	tri1	  rden;
	tri0	  wren;
